The C++ example SIMPLE (as the name says, a simple example) exist of the
following files:

 - simplepp.cpp   C++ source file

It simply shows a menu for compiling, infering, ..., of knowledge bases
using the C++ wrapping class RICE, and the fact that you can use C++ code
within the code linked to facts by means of a RICE linker function. For
testing you can use the knowledge base ANIMALS.KB. See file RICE.DOC for
more info on RICE itself.


